---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About & Methodology — Martin Way for People"
  description="Data sources, methodology, and contact information."
  canonicalPath="/about"
>

<main id="main-content" class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
  <a href="/" class="text-sm text-muted hover:text-ink underline mb-8 inline-block py-2">← Back to main page</a>

  <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold mb-8">About This Site</h1>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-3">Who maintains this</h2>
    <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed mb-2">
      This site is maintained by residents of Olympia's eastside. We are not affiliated with any political organization, campaign, or advocacy group.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">
      Contact: <a href="mailto:martinwayforpeople@pm.me" class="text-data underline">martinwayforpeople@pm.me</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-3">Data sources</h2>
    <div class="border border-border rounded-lg overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm min-w-[28rem]">
        <thead class="bg-paper-warm">
          <tr>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">Dataset</th>
            <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-ink">Source</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-border">
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Crash data (2015–2025)</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted"><a href="https://remoteapps.wsdot.wa.gov/highwaysafety/collision/data/portal/public/" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WSDOT Crash Data Portal<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Bus stops &amp; ridership</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Intercity Transit (schedule data &amp; public records request)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Priority crossings</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted"><a href="https://www.trpc.org/martinway" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TRPC Martin Way Crossing Strategy (June 2025)<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Corridor study</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted"><a href="https://www.trpc.org/DocumentCenter/View/8937" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">TRPC Martin Way Corridor Study (October 2021)<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Project site boundary</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Thurston County GeoData</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Safety corridor</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted"><a href="https://www.olympiawa.gov/services/transportation/index.php" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">City of Olympia Capital Facilities Plan<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a></td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">Traffic Impact Analysis</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted"><a href="https://ci-olympia-wa.smartgovcommunity.com/Blob/94c1d95e-0e0d-46c3-8836-eac6b7eb1289" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Transportation Engineering NorthWest (TENW), June 2, 2025<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a> (applicant-prepared)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted">SEPA documents</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-muted"><a href="https://ci-olympia-wa.smartgovcommunity.com/PublicNotice/PublicNoticeDetail/Index/d23d5890-c008-4476-ab1c-b2f10151846a?_conv=1" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">City of Olympia Community Planning &amp; Economic Development, Project No. 25-3357<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-3">Crash data methodology</h2>
    <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed mb-2">
      Crash data was obtained from the <a href="https://remoteapps.wsdot.wa.gov/highwaysafety/collision/data/portal/public/" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">WSDOT Crash Data Portal<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a> for Thurston County from 2015 through 2025. Three report types were queried: Total Crashes, Pedestrian Crashes, and Bicycle Crashes. Records were spatially filtered to the Martin Way corridor using a bounding box and then a manually drawn corridor polygon, and reverse-geocoded via the Google Maps Geocoding API. The final dataset contains 3,198 crash records. Per-year crash rates were cross-validated against TRPC's independently compiled data for the same corridor and period (2015–2019) and agree within 7%.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">
      Pedestrian and bicycle crashes were identified by matching collision report numbers against WSDOT's pedestrian and bicycle report types. Fatal crashes were identified by the severity field. Full methodology is documented in the exhibit filed with the appeal.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-bold mb-3">License</h2>
    <p class="text-muted text-base leading-relaxed">
      Content is licensed under <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">CC BY-SA 4.0<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>.
      Code is licensed under the <a href="https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT" class="text-data underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MIT License<span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</main>

</BaseLayout>
